-- 
Woman Arrested in London Over Phone Hacking Probe

-- B y   M i k e   H a r r i s o n
-- 
2011-07-17T12:21:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-17/woman-arrested-in-london-over-phone-hacking-probe-correct-.html
(Corrects age in first, second paragraphs after police
clarification.)  A 43-year-old woman has been
arrested by police in  London  in connection with allegations of
corruption and phone hacking, Scotland Yard said.  “At approximately 12.00 hrs a 43-year-old woman was
arrested by appointment at a London police station by officers
from Operation Weeting together with officers from Operation
Elveden,” a police statement said. “She is currently in
custody.”  The woman was arrested on suspicion of conspiring to
intercept communications, contrary to Section1(1) Criminal Law
Act 1977 and on suspicion of corruption allegations contrary to
Section 1 of the Prevention of Corruption Act 1906, according to
the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mike Harrison at 
 mharrison5@bloomberg.net  